Excellent read, I very much enjoyed it. Thank you for sharing it with us.

+Review

-Review


I think that the overall piece paints a lovely picture of life, love, and sacrifice. The emotion between the two brothers is clearly felt, even as a description of what I imagine are period-appropriate crude cave paintings. I assume that the two brothers maintain their vigil over each other as the smilodons? I enjoyed the fact that their  also included more recent weaponry, as an example of their struggle against various other peoples.

A question, however. If the guardians only react when someone touches the paintings, how were the paintings dated? Same goes for them, since I understand the process of radiocarbon dating involves at least minor damage due to sample collection.

I don't necessarily think that the piece should be revised to include this information, but it is something that stuck out at me.




As I said, this was quite lovely. An easy +1 from me.

SoullessSingularity, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.







